The Vice President of the United States was briefed on the status of the country's nuclear weapons stockpile by the Directors of the three national security laboratories. The briefing was attended by various officials, including the Secretary of Energy and representatives from the Departments of State and Defense. The briefing was part of the Administration's commitment to ensuring the safety and effectiveness of the nuclear arsenal, as well as the President's goal of a world without nuclear weapons and the ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty.